8 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Evidence Code;
providing for admissibility of certain statements in
9 certain proceedings; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
10
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2803.3 of Title 12, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A statement that purports to narrate, describe, report, or
18 explain an incident or incidents of domestic abuse as defined in
19 Section 60.1 of Title 22 of the Oklahoma Statutes:
20 1. Made by the victim of domestic abuse to a law enforcement
21 officer within one (1) week of the incident;
22 2. On an application for a protective order by the victim of
23 domestic abuse within one (1) week of the incident; or
