1 3. Given as testimony of the victim of domestic abuse made at a
2 hearing on application for a protective order,
3 shall be admissible in pre-trial or post-trial criminal and juvenile
4 delinquent domestic abuse prosecutions including preliminary
5 hearings, prosecutive merit hearings, or hearings on the revocation
6 of probation or acceleration of a deferred judgment.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
